Andrea Antonelli dies after World Supersport motorcycling crash
Italian struck by fellow rider after crashing in Moscow race World Superbike Championship races called off after crash
The Italian rider Andrea Antonelli died after a crash on the opening lap of a World Supersport Championship race at the Moscow Raceway on Sunday.
The Kawasaki Go Eleven rider lost control of his ZX-6R bike in rainy weather, said Tatiana Makhina, a spokeswoman for the Moscow Raceway organisers.
The 25-year old came off his bike and was struck by a fellow rider. He was treated by an emergency medical team but died of his injuries at the circuit's medical centre.
The race was called off as were the day's headline World Superbike Championship races.